# Application Server vs Web Server Infrastructure

This infrastructure improves availability and scalability by adding a second load balancer and separating each component onto its own server.

## Additional Elements

### Second Load Balancer (HAProxy)

A second HAProxy is added to create a load balancer cluster. This removes the load balancer as a single point of failure. If one HAProxy fails, the other can continue serving traffic.

### Dedicated Web Server

The web server is placed on its own server. Its role is to receive HTTP/HTTPS requests, serve static files, and forward dynamic requests to the application server.

### Dedicated Application Server

The application server is separated from the web server. It executes the application code, processes business logic, and generates dynamic content.

### Dedicated Database Server

The database is placed on a separate server. This improves performance, security, and allows the database to scale independently from the application.

## Web Server vs Application Server

**Web Server (Nginx):**

* Handles HTTP/HTTPS requests.
* Serves static content.
* Acts as a reverse proxy.

**Application Server:**

* Executes application code.
* Processes business logic.
* Communicates with the database.

## Benefits

* Improved high availability with a load balancer cluster.
* Better performance through component separation.
* Easier maintenance and troubleshooting.
* Independent scaling of web, application, and database servers.
* Reduced risk of one component affecting the others.


